segments.text: Not everybody, there's a half time.
Is that good?
I mean, does that help?
Well, we have so many people coming in the summers that we can do all the dissertations in the summers.
It's too much.
But I think for eight to 12 months,
I'm sure that our salaries are that much more than the average.
Is the university not on the 12-month?
Is it just the College of Education?
Really?
Well, that's my impression of it.
There are other parts of the college teaching summer sessions, but I think they're appointed especially for that.
It gives more time for research if you're not teaching.
OK, for example, in your own situation,
as a professor and trying to do research and the service, how do you balance your activity time-wise?
Well, I don't have classes on Friday, and I've been trying to do recently.
I was a weekend, night weekend, involved in kind of experimental research.
My research is sort of philosophical.
I'm good.
I've been an old poet and school inspector working on biography, not only as a genre, but as a, which we are always sharing our biographies, just as we're doing right now.
And so the intent of how we find out about others is a very important aspect of that because I was instrumental in establishing the society, the International Society of Earth.
Educational biography?
Yes.
Those are the kinds of things that I do.
Oh.
For your own self, what do you feel like?
has been Jack Campbell's contribution to the College of Education.
Oh, you know, one gets discouraged because they wonder if they've ever done any good.
We can't measure those things.
Which is we also very often, I think, understand.
They're not selling something.
It's hard to say what the contribution is.
I would like to think that it would change somebody's way of looking at teaching.
I don't know whether that could be someday.
Somebody will look back and say, I made a difference.
But this is very difficult.
I don't think we ever do as teachers.
You touch the lives, and very rarely will you have the opportunity to have people come back and say, not very rarely you will have it.
And I know that I have heard it from almost everybody that has had you in class.
And your caring for students has always been something that comes out from people.
And I think that means more than anything.
You have shown all along that you cared for students.
Yes, I think that.
I do.
I don't know if I...
that comes out, but I do really care for them, and I think the award last year was the height of my career.
I want to thank the Association of Former Students.
I want to thank you, Dr. Campbell.
I think we've covered the majority of the questions, and if I could come back with
a few specific questions later on as the work evolves.
Yes, I'll stop if you want.
Yes, I'd love to have that.
I'll just give you a little background up to the time, and then I'll come back and mention it.
That'll be wonderful.
